Overall, I would say that my heart and head are in a state of balance, and I try to make decisions that take into account both my emotions and my practical considerations.

answer:   As an ESFJ person, I would rate the extent of my agreement with the statement "You are more inclined to follow your head than your heart" as a 3.

While I do tend to be practical and pragmatic, I also value emotions and social harmony. I am empathic and sensitive to the feelings of others, and I tend to make decisions based on what will be most beneficial for everyone involved. I don't necessarily prioritize logic and rationality over emotions, but rather try to find a balance between the two. So while I may be inclined to follow my head in some situations, I also listen to my heart and consider the emotional implications of my decisions.

I prefer to take my time and consider all options before making a choice, as I value stability and predictability in my decision-making. I may also be influenced by the opinions and values of others, as I am highly empathic and cooperative.

Overall, while I may be decisive and thorough in my decision-making, I tend to be cautious and deliberate in my approach, preferring to take my time and consider all options before making a final decision.

I value my relationships and try to be a reliable and supportive friend, but I do not let the opinions of others define my self-worth.

I am more likely to be found participating in group activities and social events than creating art or expressing myself through creative means.

I value harmony and cooperation in my relationships, and I am more likely to follow my heart than my head in situations that involve people and emotions.
